.TH save
.SH NAME
save - client request for saving the game.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The save request is used by the client to save the current state of the game module and all server users.
.br
The current state of the game module will be exported to a new module file in the modules directory and the server
configuration value for the module will be set to this newly exported module.
.br
Server users will be saved in users directory.
.br
Save request contains the name of the save.
.br
The client user needs to be an admin, otherwise, the server will ignore this request and send a proper error response.
.SH JSON EXAMPLE
.nf
{
  "save": [
    "save1"
  ]
}
.SH SEE ALSO
response/error
